description.narrative:
INDICATOR 1 - # of advisers recruited to assist the MoD, # of MDLOs trained in substantive knowledge, % of increase in substantive knowledge of MDLOs, existence of a M&E system;

INDICATOR 2 - # of investment mechanisms, increase (%) of foreign investments to Kosovo;

INDICATOR 3 - increase (%) of usage of banks by remittance recipients, increase (%) of employment rate of remittance recipient adults, # of sales points for Kosovar products in target migration countries, increased # of returns, decrease (%) in percentage of households who plan to migrate

comment.narrative:
BASELINE 1 - MoD has limited capacity (lack of staff, lack of financial resources) to implement the strategy and laack substantive expertise to perform their duties as per the action plan;

BASELINE 2 - MDLOs lack substantive expertise to perform their duties as per the action plan;

BASELINE 3 - No monitoring and evaluation system in place to support implementation of the diaspora strategy;

TARGET  # 1 - Strengthened capacities of Kosovo authorities to implement the National Strategy for Diaspora 2013-2018

1.1: Improved capacities of Kosovo authorities to produce and manage information related to migration and development, including gender disaggregated data;
1.2: Improved capacities of Kosovo authorities at central and local level to implement the National Strategy for Diaspora 2013-2018;
1.3: Functioning diaspora business networks created in the main migration destination countries;
1.4: Municipal Diaspora Liaison Offices are set up and support is provided to building their capacities Kosovo-wide;
1.5: Monitoring and evaluation system is created in order to provide sustainable support for local authorities in implementation of the diaspora strategy:

TARGET  # 2 - Upscaling and consolidation of the tested models and mechanisms that facilitate migrants’ investments in Kosovo

2.1:  Completion of Piloting the selected Models/Instruments for investments;
2.2: Investment fund targeting the Kosovar diaspora in place and funded;
2.3: Economic zones targeting the Kosovar diaspora in place;

TARGET # 3 -   Improved business environment in Kosovo to facilitate development impact of migration and remittances

3.1: Kosovar producers have established links with diaspora businesses abroad, and local Kosovar products are available to the primary diaspora communities;
3.2: Sustainable mechanisms to improve livelihoods of remittance recipient families and remittance receiving communities established and supported (support to micro- and SMEs and skills development);

Diaspora Business Networks established in three (3) migration countries (Turkey, Sweden and Norway);

Two (2) advisers recruited to assist the MoD on projects’ coordination and, development of the roadmap for Diaspora Registry;

The voluntary registry has been accelerated through forums, a joint (MoD-DEED) promotion campaign and, training of over 200 MoD temporary employees on the voluntary registry process; 

The number of registered members of Diaspora increased for 300%;

Two (2) investment mechanisms established; 

Five (5) new foreign investments in production facilitated;

To date, the usage of banks by remittance recipients have increased for 25%, out of which 2.5% occurred only in year 2015;

Out of 6% increase of to date employment by the remittance recipient adults, 1.5% occurred in 2015;

One new sales point in migration countries, have been introduced and made available for Kosovar products;

description.narrative:
Relevant laws approved by the Assembly;
2015 implementation report of the SALW control and collection strategy shows considerable results;
20 representatives of law enforcements units trained in fight against convertible weapons, illicit trafficking , tracing and gun crime investigations

comment.narrative:
Due to amendments in the EU regulatory framework several law in Kosovo are under amendment;
Due to introduction of  new EU firearms strategy Kosovo small arms control and collection  strategy has to be amended or fully implemented;
Kosovo stakeholders need additional capacity in investigating complex gun crime investigations and illicit trafficking of SALW;
Last small arms survey dates from 2003

Legislation developed and or amended in accordance to UN, OSCE and EU standards;
Strategies developed according to international standards and best practices, monitored and implemented according to action plans;
Capacities of Kosovo stakeholders at specialist level on the field of firearms and explosive investigation enhanced;
Weapons and explosive related studies implemented
